3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper involves the study of combinatorial objects (codes) and their properties, which falls under the purview of discrete mathematics.
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper does not explicitly deal with computational complexity, but the study of codes and their properties often involves analyzing the computational complexity of decoding algorithms.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper does not focus on data structures and algorithms per se, but the study of codes often involves the design and analysis of algorithms for encoding and decoding.
